         <abstract>
            <p>This note continues work by the Lehmers [3], Gunderson [2], Granville and Monagan [1], and Tanner and Wagstaff [6], producing lower bounds for the prime exponent $p$ in any counterexample to the first case of Fermat's Last Theorem. We improve the estimate of the number of residues $r \operatorname{mod} p^2$ such that $r^p \equiv r \operatorname{mod} p^2$, and thereby improve the lower bound on $p$ to $7.568 \times 10^{17}$.</p>
          </abstract>
